<section class="how-section">
<div class="container">
	<div class="section-label">// how it works</div>
	<div class="flow">
		<div class="flow-step">
			<div class="flow-num">1</div>
			<div class="flow-title">Write or generate</div>
			<div class="flow-desc">Create SKILL.md files manually or auto-generate from OpenAPI specs and text descriptions.</div>
			<div class="flow-code">skillgen openapi ./api.yaml</div>
		</div>
		<div class="flow-step">
			<div class="flow-num">2</div>
			<div class="flow-title">Validate and score</div>
			<div class="flow-desc">Lint for secrets, validate against the spec, and get a 0â€“100 quality score across 5 dimensions.</div>
			<div class="flow-code">skill-tools check ./skills/</div>
		</div>
		<div class="flow-step">
			<div class="flow-num">3</div>
			<div class="flow-title">Route at runtime</div>
			<div class="flow-desc">BM25 full-text search picks the right skill from thousands. No API keys, no GPU, instant results.</div>
			<div class="flow-code">router.select('deploy my app')</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
</section>

<style>
	.how-section { padding: 0; }

	.flow {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.flow-step {
		padding: 1.25rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}

	.flow-num {
		font-size: 0.65rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--blue);
		background: var(--blue-bg);
		border: 1px solid var(--blue-border);
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 22px;
		height: 22px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.flow-title {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
	}

	.flow-desc {
		font-family: var(--font-body);
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.flow-code {
		margin-top: 0.6rem;
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		color: var(--blue);
		background: var(--bg2);
		padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		display: inline-block;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.flow { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>
